value: B - "very loud" when listening. Guitar on A felt like it was competeing a bit more. On B can hear more plosives and breath (but personal prefence). Feels natural in B.
Snare a little too harsh in A, cymbals and vocal fight for space in 6-7kHz range. Selected - instantly more lowend in the bass, top end of snare is a bit smoother.
Guitars mixed a bit better in chosen, could hear more clarity.
Both very similar. Selected had more bass on bass guitar, but other than that everything in both felt the same. In both, snare was in the way of vocal in high mids.
Felt vocals had more presence in B.
Selected's vocal balance was better, everything seemed a bit more full.
Sounded more like the original than them all. Had more guitar presence which quite liked in selected.

More balanced mix with B, A sounded good but vocals got lost in second half again. B vocals were much more consistent, both volume and frequency wise. The other instruments in A clashed too much with the vocals.
Parts of A preffered over B and vice versa, but B overall slightly. Little more low end and vocal presence in B.
